This paper deals with relation extraction, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also makes use of knowledge graph embeddings, which are a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) for representing structured data. Additionally, the paper uses graph convolution networks, which are a type of neural network commonly used in graph-based machine learning tasks such as recommendation systems and social network analysis, falling under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with large-scale datasets, which may require efficient database management techniques, making it relevant to the database (cs.DB) subcategory.
